                <h1>Sylvia Plath's "The Yellow Wallpaper": A Study of Gender & Mental Health</h1>
                <p>Sylvia Plath's *The Yellow Wallpaper* is a poignant exploration of mental illness, gender roles, and personal liberation. The narrative revolves around a woman's descent into madness, trapped in a room with disturbing wallpaper that symbolizes her confinement. Plath’s vivid imagery and deep emotional resonance make this story a timeless reflection on freedom and identity.</p>
